review_blob: I was expecting more on the nose. A bit more carbonated than I expected, but this wasnt a bad thing. Notes of Banana, caramel, butterscotch, ginger, raisin, vanilla, woody, smoke and nuts. It was nice, but as I understand the beer was to be released with the launch of the Honest Burgers in Brewdog bars and can see it pairing really nicely with one of those.
Lovely beer with Caramel, nuts, roasted coffee flavours. Theres an some initial alcohol and an aftertaste of licorice, smoke and chocolate.
